{
  "doc_id": "54533",
  "text": "Numerous reports describe seasonal changes in the contents of flavonoid and phenolic acid derivatives in various plant species [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Although a variety of different accumulation patterns were observed, it is often stated in the literature that seasonal changes in phenolic acids contents follow a trend that is frequently the opposite to the direction of changes in flavonoid glycosides concentration. To investigate the seasonal variability of flavonoids and phenolic acids in P. officinalis, we first applied the untargeted metabolomics approach.",
